\[ \text{Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio} = \frac{\text{Cash Flow from Operating Activities}}{\text{Net Income}} \]

\[
\frac{-18,924,462.44}{1,842,166.21} \approx -10.27
\]

Since the ratio is negative, indicating operating cash flows are significantly negative compared to net income, we will express it accordingly.
